===Parrott's emotions by groups=== A [[Tree structure|tree-structured]] list of emotions was described in Shaver et al. (1987),<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Shaver, P.|author2=Schwartz, J.|author3=Kirson, D.|author4=O'connor, C.|lastauthoramp=y|year=1987|title=Emotion knowledge: further exploration of a prototype approach|journal=Journal of Personality and Social Psychology|volume=52|issue=6|page=1061|pmid=3598857|doi=10.1037/0022-3514.52.6.1061}}</ref> and also featured in Parrott (2001).<ref>{{cite book|author=Parrott, W.|year=2001|title=Emotions in Social Psychology|publisher=Psychology Press|location=Philadelphia|isbn=978-0863776830|series=Key Readings in Social Psychology}}</ref> {|class="wikitable" |- ! Primary emotion ! Secondary emotion ! Tertiary emotion |- |rowspan="3"|[[Love]]||''[[Affection]]||''[[Adoration]]{{·}}[[Fondness]]{{·}}[[Reciprocal liking|Liking]]{{·}}[[Attractiveness|Attraction]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:caring|Caring]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:tenderness|Tenderness]]{{·}}[[Compassion]]{{·}}[[Sentimentality]]'' |- |''[[Lust]]/[[Sexual attraction|Sexual desire]]||''[[Desire (emotion)|Desire]]{{·}}[[Passion (emotion)|Passion]]{{·}}[[Infatuation]]'' |- |''[[Wiktionary:longing|Longing]]||''Longing'' |- |rowspan="7"|[[Joy]]||''[[Cheerfulness]]||''[[Amusement]]{{·}}[[wikt:bliss|Bliss]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:gaiety|Gaiety]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:glee|Glee]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:jolliness|Jolliness]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:joviality|Joviality]]{{·}}[[Joy]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:delight|Delight]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:enjoyment|Enjoyment]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:gladness|Gladness]]{{·}}[[Happiness]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:jubilation|Jubilation]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:elation|Elation]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:satisfation|Satisfaction]]{{·}}[[Ecstasy (emotion)|Ecstasy]]{{·}}[[Euphoria]]'' |- |''[[Zest (positive psychology)|Zest]]||''[[Enthusiasm]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:zeal|Zeal]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:excitement|Excitement]]{{·}}[[Wiktionary:thrill|Thrill]]{{·}}[[Exhilaration]]'' |- |''[[Contentment]]||''[[Pleasure]]'' |- |''[[Pride