'''Eustachio Porcellotti''' ([[19th century]]) was a Florentine [[watchmaker]].<ref name=imss>{{cite web|url=http://brunelleschi.imss.fi.it/galileopalazzostrozzi/object/EustachioPorcellottiGalileosPendulumClock.html |title=Eustachio Porcellotti, Galileo’s pendulum clock |publisher=Brunelleschi.imss.fi.it |date= |accessdate=2016-06-23}}</ref>
He was known for having built, in the second half of the [[19th century]], several models illustrating the Galilean notion of applying the pendulum to the [[clock]].<ref name=imss/>
