{{Other uses|Scorcher (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox book | name = Scorcher: The Dirty Politics of Climate Change | image = Scorcher - The Dirty Politics of Climate Change.jpeg | caption = | author = [[Clive Hamilton]] | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | subject = [[Howard Government]], [[Kyoto Protocol]] | genre = | publisher = Black Inc. Agenda | pub_date = 2007 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 266 pp. | isbn = 978-0-9775949-0-0 | oclc = 155147488 | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Scorcher: The Dirty Politics of Climate Change''''' is a 2007 book by [[Clive Hamilton]] which contends that Australia rather than the United States is the [[Politics of global warming|major stumbling block]] to a more effective [[Kyoto Protocol]]. In the final chapter of the book Hamilton argues that "the [[Howard Government]] has been actively working to destroy the Kyoto Protocol".<ref>[[Tim Flannery]]. [http://www.theage.com.au/news/book-reviews/scorcher-the-dirty-politics-of-climate-change/2007/05/25/1179601645988.html Scorcher: the dirty politics of climate change] ''The Age'', May 25, 2007.</ref>
Scorcher is an updated version of Hamilton's 2001 book, ''Running from the Storm''. Other books by Clive Hamilton include ''[[Requiem for a Species]]'', ''[[Silencing Dissent]]'', ''[[Growth Fetish]]'', ''[[Affluenza]]'' and ''[[The Freedom Paradox: Towards a Post-Secular Ethics|The Freedom Paradox]]''.
==Quotes== *"In the tight little world of greenhouse lobbying, the Prime Minister saw nothing improper in going to the country's biggest greenhouse polluters to ask them what the Government should do about greenhouse policy, without extending the same opportunity to other industries, not to mention environment groups and independent experts".<ref name=wf>Wendy Frew. [http://www.smh.com.au/news/book-reviews/scorcher-the-dirty-politics-of-climate-change/2007/05/16/1178995222073.html?page=fullpage#contentSwap1 Scorcher: the dirty politics of climate change] ''The Sydney Morning Herald'', May 16, 2007.</ref>
==See also== {{portal|Global warming}}
* ''[[An Inconvenient Truth]]'' – a 2006 documentary featuring [[Al Gore]] * ''[[Climate Code Red: The Case for Emergency Action]]'' – a 2008 book from Australia on climate change * [[Greenhouse Mafia]] * [[List of Australian environmental books]] * [[Politics of global warming]] * ''[[Storms of my Grandchildren]]'' – a 2009 book by climate scientist [[James Hansen]]
